One might suspect that Hesiod was the first to look for such a thing-or some one else who put love or desire among existing things as a principle. Parmenides also does this. for he, in constructing the genesis of the universe, says:- &quot;
&ldquo;Love first of all the Gods she planned. &quot;
Hesiod says:
"First of all things was chaos made, and then "Broad-breasted earth... "And love, 'mid all the gods pre-eminent, "
